{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"bonelike-facile-inganue","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nRead-only derivations over the durable ticket event store (including compaction-retired `.retired` events) computing the agent-process metrics with complete history: attempts/claims per ticket, first-pass verification rate, rework at 7/30 days, recovery windows, orchestrator-replanning (post-claim decomposition change), escalation, revert+follow-up-fix, and handoff / handoff-failure.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/event_metrics.py` — new: functions taking a date range + the reduced/raw stream, registered in `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_event_metrics.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nThe event store already witnesses these structurally, so no new emission is needed: STATUS->in_progress events (durable via `.retired`, read with `reduce_ticket(..., include_retired=True)` from `src/rebar/reducer/_api.py`) carry the claiming `session`, so attempts = distinct claim sessions; reopen->close within a window = rework; a REVERT/reopen/`Verified -1` -> next fixing event = recovery; post-claim CREATE/LINK/UNLINK under an in-progress epic = replanning; `caused_by` links let recovery span tickets. HLC timestamps are real wall-clock ns, so bucketing is exact. Pure read-side; nothing written.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (real temp store fixtures of crafted events): a ticket claimed by two distinct sessions yields attempts=2; a reopen->close 3 days apart is rework-within-7; a clean close is first-pass.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_event_metrics.py` passes: attempts over a 2-distinct-session fixture returns 2 (`assert m == 2`); reopen-within-7 is counted and reopen-within-40 is excluded from the 7-day series.\n- [ ] first-pass rate over one clean close + one fail-then-pass returns 0.5 — unit test asserts the exact ratio.\n- [ ] compaction-retired claim events are included via `include_retired=True`: the post-compaction attempt count equals the pre-compaction count — unit test asserts equality.","id":"18e6-4bfb-1dcf-4a37","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Event-derivation readers (agent-process metrics over the durable event store)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416750080483001,"uuid":"765028e1-70ce-4a96-8242-87e73bea5c0b"}